claim.claim-text:
A fluid flow system comprising:
a first radial fluid device comprising:
a cylinder block comprising a first plurality of radially extending cylinders, a second plurality of radially extending cylinders, and a shaft opening;
a first plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the second plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a first cam disposed about the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second cam disposed about the second plurality of radially extending cylinders, the second cam movable relative to the first cam;
an input shaft coupled to the cylinder block at the shaft opening, the input shaft operable to transmit rotational energy to the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device;
a second radial fluid device comprising:
a cylinder block comprising a first plurality of radially extending cylinders, a second plurality of radially extending cylinders, and a shaft opening;
a first plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the second plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a first cam disposed about the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second cam disposed about the second plurality of radially extending cylinders, the second cam movable relative to the first cam; and
a coupling device coupling the shaft opening of the second radial fluid device to the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device opposite the shaft opening of the first radial fluid device, the coupling device operable to transmit rotational energy from the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device to the cylinder block of the second radial fluid device.

A radial fluid device comprising:
a cylinder block comprising a first plurality of radially extending cylinders, a second plurality of radially extending cylinders; a first plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the second plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a first cam disposed about the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second cam disposed about the second plurality of radially extending cylinders, the second cam movable relative to the first cam; and
a coupling device operable to couple the cylinder block to a cylinder block of a second radial fluid device.

The fluid flow system of claim 12, the cam rotation device of the first radial fluid device comprising:
a first worm gear in contact with the first cam of the first radial fluid device;
a first reverse rotation gear coupled to the first worm gear;
a second worm gear in contact with the second cam of the first radial fluid device; and
a second reverse rotation gear coupled to the second worm gear and in contact with the first reverse rotation gear, or
the radial fluid device of claim 2 comprising:
a first worm gear in contact with the first cam;
a first reverse rotation gear coupled to the first worm gear;
a second worm gear in contact with the second cam; and
a second reverse rotation gear coupled to the second worm gear and in contact with the first reverse rotation gear.

A method of installing a fluid flow system, comprising:
providing a first radial fluid device comprising:
a cylinder block comprising a first plurality of radially extending cylinders, a second plurality of radially extending cylinders, and a shaft opening;
a first plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the second plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a first cam disposed about the first plurality of radially extending cylinders; and
a second cam disposed about the second plurality of radially extending cylinders, the second cam movable relative to the first cam;
providing a second radial fluid device comprising:
a cylinder block comprising a first plurality of radially extending cylinders, a second plurality of radially extending cylinders, and a shaft opening;
a first plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the first plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a second plurality of pistons each slidably received within a different one of the second plurality of radially extending cylinders;
a first cam disposed about the first plurality of radially extending cylinders; and
a second cam disposed about the second plurality of radially extending cylinders, the second cam movable relative to the first cam;
coupling an input shaft coupled to the cylinder block at the shaft opening, the input shaft operable to transmit rotational energy to the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device; and
coupling the shaft opening of the second radial fluid device to the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device opposite the shaft opening of the first radial fluid device such that the cylinder block of the first radial fluid device transmits rotational energy to the cylinder block of the second radial fluid device.
